headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 38 points and led a third-quarter surge that sent the Boston Celtics past the Atlanta Hawks 105-95 Sunday for their eighth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum scores 38, Celtics rally past Hawks for 8th win in row

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards celebrated a milestone Sunday by scoring 37 points and leading the Minnesota Timberwolves to a 129-120 victory over the Indiana Pacers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edwards' milestone game leads Timberwolves over Pacers
